Some notes regarding the above code.
1. It is recommended to use [Java naming conventions][1] which means that method `BuildGui` should be named `buildGui`.
2. It is usually better to set one of the dimensions to 0 (zero) in the `GridLayout` constructor. Refer to [How to Use GridLayout][2].
3. Most of the &quot;listener&quot; interfaces have a corresponding &quot;adapter&quot; class that implements the interface. For `MouseListener` there is class `MouseAdapter`. This saves you from having to write implementations for every method in the listener interface. Refer to [How to Write a Mouse Listener][3].
4. Usually you would add an `ActionListener` to a `JButton`, rather than a `MouseListener`. Refer to [How to Use Buttons, Check Boxes, and Radio Buttons][4]. But I assume that your professor has a reason for setting the assignment requirements.

