Your problem is not about precision. By default `double`s in Java have a fixed precision which is far greater than 2 decimal places. I.E. the value is stored with more than 2 decimal places by default.&lt;br&gt;
You can also take a look at [**this**][1] question&lt;br&gt;
It seems to me that you are looking for a way to represent only 2 decimal digits. One way is by using `printf`

For example:

    System.out.printf(&quot;%.2f&quot;, 0.2);

This will print:

`0.20`

Hope this helps


